.SH NAME
.PP
wolfictl\-vet \- Vet a melange or apko manifest before sending to PR


.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBwolfictl vet [manifest.yaml] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Vet a melange or apko manifest before sending to PR.

.PP
This command runs a series of checks on the given manifest file:
.IP "1." 4
Identifies the manifest type (melange or apko)
.IP "2." 4
Runs format check (wolfictl lint yam)
.IP "3." 4
Runs lint check (wolfictl lint)
.IP "4." 4
Optionally runs melange or apko pipeline if enabled

.PP
Example:
.PP
.RS

.nf
  wolfictl vet my\-melange\-manifest.yaml
  wolfictl vet my\-apko\-manifest.yaml \-\-run\-melange\-pipeline
  wolfictl vet my\-apko\-manifest.yaml \-\-run\-apko\-pipeline

.fi
.RE


.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP[=false]
    help for vet

.PP
\fB\-\-run\-apko\-pipeline\fP[=false]
    Run apko pipeline (build, scan)

.PP
\fB\-\-run\-melange\-pipeline\fP[=false]
    Run melange pipeline (keygen, build, scan)

.PP
\fB\-\-temp\-dir\fP=""
    Temporary directory for build artifacts (default: system temp directory)

.PP
\fB\-\-verbose\fP[=false]
    Enable verbose output


.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Run basic checks on a single manifest:

.PP
.RS

.nf
wolfictl vet my\-package.yaml

.fi
.RE

.PP
Run the full melange build + scan locally (useful before pushing large changes):

.PP
.RS

.nf
wolfictl vet \-\-run\-melange\-pipeline packages/my\-package.yaml

.fi
.RE

.PP
Lint several manifests in one go:

.PP
.RS

.nf
wolfictl vet pkg1.yaml pkg2.yaml pkg3.yaml

.fi
.RE

.PP
Store build artifacts in a custom directory and enable verbose logging:

.PP
.RS

.nf
wolfictl vet \-\-run\-apko\-pipeline \-\-temp\-dir ./artifacts \-\-verbose images/webserver.yaml

.fi
.RE


